How to use this correctly (this is the skill)

Treat it like a wargame, not reality.

When you “run OrbitOS in your head”:

Do this:
	1.	Define the actors (roughly)
	•	aligned / opposed / neutral
	•	stable / volatile
	•	high / low influence
	2.	Estimate current trajectory
	•	where are they heading?
	3.	Apply an interaction
	•	what force are you introducing?
	4.	Project 1–2 steps forward
	•	not 10 steps
	•	keep it short horizon
	5.	Check alternatives
	•	what if opposite action?
	•	what if no action?

That’s enough.

