The key limitation (this keeps you sharp)

Mental simulations fail when:
	•	you assume too much hidden knowledge
	•	you overextend time horizon
	•	you treat outputs as certainty instead of scenarios
	•	you forget that humans can break pattern on a whim

So always treat outputs as:

plausible trajectories, not predictions

